misconceptions.inferred_category_name: No misconception detected (correct wrap-around right shift)
misconceptions.student_thought_process: The student believes that to right-shift with wrap-around, you must (1) save the last element, (2) shift elements from the end toward the front to avoid overwriting needed values, and (3) place the saved last element into index 0.
misconceptions.conceptual_gap: No gap: this matches Java’s actual array assignment behavior and avoids overwrite by iterating from high to low indices.
